snippet: James McGee, ranked No. 214 in the world, has competed in 26 countries and territories since the start of the 2012 season and lacks funding for a coach.
abstract: Profile of Irish tennis player James McGee, ranked 214 overall, whose experience exemplifies the travails of lower-rung professionals; McGee, who has crisscrossed world competing in 26 countries and territories since 2012, lacks funding for a coach.
lead_paragraph: James McGee, ranked No. 214 in the world, has competed in 26 countries and territories since the start of the 2012 season and lacks funding for a coach.

headline.main: Lonely at the Top? Try the Lower Rungs of Professional Tennis
headline.print_headline: Lonely at the Top? Try the Lower Rungs
